South African developer RogueCode has released Vicious Attack Llama Apocalypse on Steam. The game is being sold for R105, with an 11% discount for the first week of launch. Vicious Attack Llama Apocalypse is a top-down shooter where you remotely pilot an endless supply of mechs from your carrier ship. The aim is to fight through the llama hordes to take down The Llamanati. RogueCode’s Matt Cavanagh said the game will also be released for Xbox One and the Windows Store on 16 March, and will support Xbox Play Anywhere. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>